## SEO Implementation Status

### Metadata (all sites)
- All 236 posts have populated canonicals matching their URL pattern
- metaTitles: optimized for CTR, under 60 chars, keyword front-loaded, year references (2026 or 2026/27) on time-sensitive topics
- metaDescriptions: fact-led openers (no "Complete guide to..." filler), under 155 chars, specific numbers/outcomes
- openGraph: includes title, description, type, url, siteName, publishedTime, images (dynamic OG fallback)
- Twitter cards: summary_large_image on all blog posts and static pages

### Schema (JSON-LD)
- BlogPosting + FAQPage (when faqs present) on all blog posts via `buildBlogPostingJsonLd()`
- Person author: `"{Brand} Editorial Team"` with /about URL
- Organization publisher with absolute logo URL
- BreadcrumbList on blog posts and category pages
- LocalBusiness on location pages (absolute logo URL)
- CollectionPage on category hub pages

### Internal Linking
- Property: 85/85 posts have 2-3 internal links each (255 total: inline contextual + Related Reading sections)
- Medical: 46/46 posts have 2-3 internal links each (~158 total)
- Dentists: 44/55 posts have internal links (pre-existing, using flat URLs that redirect via middleware)
- Solicitors: 47/50 posts have internal links (pre-existing)

### AI Discoverability
- `llms.txt` in all 4 sites' public/ directories (site description, key pages, categories, sitemap)
- `robots.ts` explicitly allows GPTBot, ClaudeBot, Google-Extended, PerplexityBot, CCBot on all sites

### Redirects
- Property/Dentists/Solicitors have `permanentRedirect` logic in `[category]/[slug]/page.tsx`: if a slug exists under a different category than the URL, it 301-redirects to the correct URL
- Dentists has `middleware.ts` mapping old flat /blog/{slug} URLs to /blog/{category}/{slug}

